From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 21 Jun 2026 17:43:18 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] find: run -exec/-execdir commands through brush, not exec
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Ports find's -exec actions to dispatch through `Shell::run_argv` (the same
`builtin_exec` bridge xargs now uses), so `find … -exec cmd …` runs a shell
builtin, a function, or a script — all snooped — exactly like xargs and
env/nice. Before, `find -exec <function>` / `-exec <builtin>` were "command not
found".

Fork side: `Dependencies` gains `exec_via_shell()` + `run(argv, cwd)`. The
embedder sets `exec_via_shell() == true`, so both matchers route the
fully-substituted argv through `run` instead of spawning a `std::process::
Command`:
  - SingleExecMatcher (`-exec … \;`/`-execdir`): builds the argv, runs it with
    cwd = the entry's parent for -execdir (`exec_dir_cwd`), else the logical
    cwd (None — the subshell already has it).
  - MultiExecMatcher (`-exec … +`): `argmax` exists only for the OS exec
    arg-limit, which doesn't apply in-process, so the shell path just
    accumulates matched paths in `pending` and flushes one command per batch
    (a directory for -execdir at finished_dir, the whole run for -exec at
    finished). A non-zero exit sets find's exit code, as before.
The standalone binary (`exec_via_shell() == false`) keeps its Command/argmax
path untouched.

Builtin side: FindBuiltin becomes an async `builtins::Command`; find runs on a
worker thread submitting each -exec argv over the bridge, the executor runs it
on a subshell clone (per-command cwd for -execdir) and replies. -exec is serial
so the thread blocks per reply. The bridge gained an optional per-command cwd
for -execdir.

Verified in a box shim: -exec a function ("fn-got:./a.txt"), -exec a builtin
(`type`), -exec + batch (one call, all paths), -execdir \; and + (each batch in
its own directory with ./relative paths), external -exec cat, plain -print and
relative {} display. xargs unregressed; 93 engine tests pass.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01B5MwFcipu6iwqtMPPwFhXd
